        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 18928] Missing pieces in the C API for environments*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18928>\n\n--- Comment #2 from Lionel Henry (<mailto:lionel.hry@gmail.com|lionel.hry@gmail.com>) ---\nTo support iterating over environments, we'd need one of these additions:\n\n**A symbol-returning variant of `R_lsInternal`**\n\nCurrently `R_lsInternal` returns a character vector, but the environment\nbinding API takes symbols. Once we have the list of symbols, we can iterate\nover it with env accessors. A variant returning a list of symbols would be more\nergonomic. Sorting is not needed for this use case.\n\n**An environment mapper**\n\nThis could be an opaque iterator object (similar to the [dots iterator\nproposal](<https:\/\/gist.github.com\/lionel-\/1ebcbd5ec69c0775d514c329522408a3#iterating-over-dots>)).\nThis would have the advantage that the iterator could pass binding values\ndirectly to avoid redundant lookups. However, a simpler mapper like\n`R_mapAttrib()` would also be fine. The callback would receive the symbol and\nbinding type, then look up the binding value itself:\n\n```\nvoid callback(SEXP sym, R_BindingType type, void* data) {\n    switch (type) {\n    case R_BindingTypeValue:\n        \/\/ Use e.g. Rf_findVarInFrame3()\n        break;\n    case R_BindingTypeDelayed:\n        \/\/ Use e.g. R_DelayedBindingExpression() etc.\n        break;\n    \/\/ ...\n    }\n}\n\nR_mapEnvBindings(env, callback, data);\n```",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1770215185.763199",
        "bot_id": "B06769YJX9Q",
        "app_id": "A024R9PQM",
