                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18928"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\n--- Comment #2 from Lionel Henry ("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "mailto:lionel.hry@gmail.com",
                                "text": "lionel.hry@gmail.com"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") ---\nTo support iterating over environments, we'd need one of these additions:\n\n**A symbol-returning variant of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "R_lsInternal",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "**\n\nCurrently "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "R_lsInternal",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " returns a character vector, but the environment\nbinding API takes symbols. Once we have the list of symbols, we can iterate\nover it with env accessors. A variant returning a list of symbols would be more\nergonomic. Sorting is not needed for this use case.\n\n**An environment mapper**\n\nThis could be an opaque iterator object (similar to the [dots iterator\nproposal]("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/gist.github.com\/lionel-\/1ebcbd5ec69c0775d514c329522408a3#iterating-over-dots"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ")).\nThis would have the advantage that the iterator could pass binding values\ndirectly to avoid redundant lookups. However, a simpler mapper like\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "R_mapAttrib()",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " would also be fine. The callback would receive the symbol and\nbinding type, then look up the binding value itself:\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "void callback(SEXP sym, R_BindingType type, void* data) {\n    switch (type) {\n    case R_BindingTypeValue:\n        \/\/ Use e.g. Rf_findVarInFrame3()\n        break;\n    case R_BindingTypeDelayed:\n        \/\/ Use e.g. R_DelayedBindingExpression() etc.\n        break;\n    \/\/ ...\n    }\n}\n\nR_mapEnvBindings(env, callback, data);\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
