        "text": "*[Bug 18998] New: add Rd macro '\\linkS4methods' parallel to '\\linkS4class'*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18998>\n\n            Bug ID: 18998\n           Summary: add Rd macro '\\linkS4methods' parallel to\n                    '\\linkS4class'\n           Product: R\n           Version: R-devel (trunk)\n          Hardware: Other\n                OS: Other\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: normal\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Wishlist\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:jaganmn@mcmaster.ca|jaganmn@mcmaster.ca>\n\nPackages often document S4 methods in help with `\\alias{genericname-methods}`. \nIf the generic (or made-generic) function lives in a different package, then\npackages often do *not* add `\\alias{genericname}`, so that\n`help(\"genericname\")` remains unambiguous.  Indeed, `methods::promptMethods`\npromotes this convention:\n\n```\n&gt; setGeneric(\"norm\")\n&gt; cat(paste0(promptMethods(\"norm\", NA)$aliases, \"\\n\", collapse = \"\"))\n\\alias{norm-methods}\n\\alias{norm,ANY,ANY-method}\n\\alias{norm,ANY,missing-method}\n```\n\nIt follows that if one wants to link method documentation and not generic\nfunction documentation, then generally one must link `genericname-methods` and\nnot `genericname`.  Very often one does that like so:\n\n```\n\\link[=genericname-methods]{genericname}\n```\n\nThat is a bit too cumbersome for me, so in some S4-using packages I define a\nnew macro\n\n```\n\\newcommand{\\linkS4methods}{\\link[=#1-methods]{#1}}\n```\n\nand I type `\\linkS4methods{genericname}`.\n\nMy wish is that R can start to support `\\linkS4methods` out of the box, exactly\nas it supports `\\linkS4class`.  If people agree, then I could develop a patch\nfor **tools** and WRE.\n\nNote that I ask now because I see:\n\n```\n&gt; db &lt;- news(grepl(\"\\\\linkS4class\", Text))\n&gt; print(db, doBrowse = FALSE)\n                           Changes in R-devel                           \n\nNEW FEATURES\n\n    o   In *.Rd help files, the \\linkS4class macro now also works for\n        links to other packages via \\linkS4class[&lt;pkg&gt;]{&lt;myClass&gt;},\n        much nicer than the \"workaround\"\n        \\link[&lt;pkg&gt;:&lt;myClass&gt;-class]{&lt;myClass&gt;} necessary in earlier\n        versions of R.\n\n        Packages with the new syntax need to formally depend on R &gt;=\n        4.6.0.\n```\n\nIdeally, addition of `\\linkS4methods` would coincide with recent improvements\nto `\\linkS4class`.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
